# scripts/dev/ — developer tools (lint, test, generate, reset-db, ...)
#
# This directory is intentionally separate from scripts/ops/, which holds
# host-operations scripts (configure env, build images, run containers).
#
# What's the difference?
#   scripts/ops/<X>/<script>.sh   operates on a host (CMS / dev target /
#                                  prod target) — produces or consumes images
#                                  and containers.
#   scripts/dev/<script>.sh       runs on the developer's machine as part of
#                                  their inner loop — lint, format, test,
#                                  seed data, reset local DB, etc.
#
# Convention:
#   - Every script here must be runnable WITHOUT docker (no compose, no
#     container lifecycle).
#   - Output is local-only (developer machine state, not any host).
#   - Add a .gitkeep-less file when you add your first tool — remove this
#     stub at that point.